300 1608 760 (The most serious problems with injection are) 760 SB
300 1721 43 (1. ) 75 SB
375 1721 1547 (When the first instantiation of the enclosing class occurs, it is possible that a name that was) 1547 SB
375 1771 1378 (previously declared to be a type, suddenly becomes a function \(as is the case with ) 1378 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 33 /Courier /font0 ANSIFont font
1753 1776 25 (f) 25 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
1778 1771 286 ( in the example\).) 286 SB
300 1886 43 (2. ) 75 SB
375 1886 1718 (The point at which a particular version of a function is declared is difficult to predict.  It is possible to) 1718 SB
375 1936 1679 (construct cases whose meaning changes when the point of instantiation of a class changes from one) 1679 SB
375 1986 281 (place to another.) 281 SB
32 0 0 58 58 0 0 0 53 /Helvetica-Bold /font13 ANSIFont font
300 2099 64 (2. ) 78 SB
378 2099 1292 (The History of Name Injection and X3J16/WG21) 1292 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
300 2181 1798 (Three years ago, the WP was not clear on the subject of name injection.  Existing practice was unanimous,) 1798 SB
300 2231 1800 (however.  Injections occurred as part of the instantiation of the enclosing class.  Some committee members) 1800 SB
300 2281 1667 (were concerned, however, because of the fact that a program\222s behavior can depend on the point of) 1667 SB
300 2331 1786 (instantiation of a class.  This is a concern because it can be very difficult to know exactly where that point) 1786 SB
300 2381 1673 (is.  In San Jose, the Extensions WG decided to clarify that injection was supposed to occur, but this) 1673 SB
300 2431 1749 (decision was put on hold pending further discussion.  The subject was discussed further, and at the next) 1749 SB
300 2481 1792 (meeting, in San Diego, the Extensions WG proposed that a program attempts to inject something that was) 1792 SB
300 2531 623 (not previously declared is ill-formed.) 623 SB
300 2631 1693 (This decision was itself controversial because it affected existing code and disallowed certain coding) 1693 SB
300 2681 1777 (practices without providing an alternative.  More than a 1.5 years later, after numerous discussions of the) 1777 SB
300 2731 1139 (subject, a motion to restore injection was approved in Valley Forge.) 1139 SB
300 2831 1699 (More than 1.5 years has passed since Valley Forge, and the subject of injection has been discussed at) 1699 SB
300 2881 1673 (virtually every meeting since.  There is now a proposal from Bill Gibbons \(N0878\) to replace name) 1673 SB
